Alexander Zverev produced an impressive display to beat Dominic Thiem in straight sets on Saturday and book his spot in the Madrid Open final. Fifth seed Zverev, who stunned five-time champion, Rafael Nadal, in the quarterfinals on Friday, saw off Thiem 6-3, 6-4 in a repeat of 2018 final, which was also won by the German. “It is going to mean a lot to me (if I can win the final) I am definitely looking forward to it,” said the 24-year-old Zverev, bidding to win the title without dropping a set, as he did three years ago.